ools for a dozen years. &#10;If we were to adopt the voucher system then schools would be forced to compete. Better schools would attract more students, they'd generate more ADA and prosper. Then the less successful schools would be forced to provide a better product. The result is that the quality of education across the board would improve. This would cost no more money that it does now. Teachers hate this plan because it means that they'd have to work harder and innovate; something that many teachers are not wont to do. &#10;We have paid for public schools since we achieved Independence from Britain. The reason that we do this that a Republic cannot function without an enlightened electorate. We want people to be able to read and make intelligent decisions concerning the operation of our government. &#10;Today it's questionable that this is being done."/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1162" language="en" documentId="4797" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Logjam" date="7th November 2006 05:24 PM" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://www.volconvo.com/forums/showthread.php?t=12481&amp;page=6" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="4797" notes="" title="Public Schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="331"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="332" end="832"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="833" end="1113"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="1114" end="1162"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>